As a woman who has worked in the modeling and talent industries swimming with gorgeous men of all types for decades, I would say most of the comments here about John K's looks are either too unfavorable and made by insecure individuals, or too fangirl-ish and inaccurately overly-complimentary at the opposite end of the spectrum. When John was on "The Office", had he not been playing the role of the "Aw Shucks"-unrequited and ultimately triumphant suitor of Pam, and just been another regular cubicle worker, he certainly would not have been as noticed or highly-regarded by women or men. So he definitely benefitted by the show writers' largesse and arc of his character, there. And he's since built upon that image very well, even in "non-love" roles.  Also, John's physical look as a man is definitely "high-average" 6+ on a scale of 10(yes, women have those too for men lol). But, his then unstable, fluff and comb it forward hairline in his early career(which he has since thickened up and "fixed" now that he's a millionaire), and his somewhat "box-jaw/slight double-chin"(we used to call that the "Fred Flintstone"-chin lol), was definitely a detraction to his overall look. If you notice now, John is pretty set on wearing a beard, which I believe, hides those less than attractive facial features. Plus, beards are in style and add to his "rugged manliness"-appeal.  His eyes are very pretty. Almost unnnaturally so. That is undeniable. And he knows just how to flash them in that enthusiastic, "happy over the small things"-way, that most women swoon over, unless they're an unmovable, Ingmar Bergman film binge-watching, perpetual Goth chick with black eyeliner on her soul.   Now, onto the hard part ~ It's not telling tales out of school to recognize the fact that John is a very tall man. Offically listed at 6'3" but, he appears much taller than that in film and talk show appearances. Height for most women in judging men, is like bosom size for men in judging women. There are undeniable, evolutionarily-biological components of attraction there, that cannot be ignored. Many things can be overlooked by a woman in judging a man, if a he's tall. Sorry guys and women who deny this out of fear as being perceived as being "shallow", but for the most part it's absolutely true.  Having said that, and recognizing the obvious edge John has over 70% of the U.S male population that isn't over 6'2", it's also very fair to say that theoretically if John Krasinski were as proportionally attractive with the same show biz cachet, money and with the same features but scaled down to a 5'9"-tall man, at least 60% of the women here who "swoon" over John K, would simply not be doing so and even if they were, there would be serious caveats to their attraction.    The only guys who can get away with being "short" in the entertainment industry and still be seen as sex symbols and attract women above their pay grade, are rock stars. My .02 and assessment. Rip me to shreds, if you will. It still won't change the relative subjective truth in what I said.
